course.subject: BIEN
course.name: Bioengineering Laboratory
course.description: This course provides hands-on experience with molecular biotechnology, biomolecular engineering, biosensors, biomedical devices, and bioanalytical techniques. Laboratory experiments including cell culture, genetic engineering techniques, bioanalytical methods, biosensors and biomedical devices, with additional emphasis on data analysis. For students of the CBE department only.
course.prerequisites: BIEN 2410 AND BIEN 2610
